  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Space
  slugs are large silicon-based organisms that can survive in the airless
  vacuum of space.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>They are typically
  found lurking in asteroid fields, or sometimes at barren rock planets. Sp=
ace
  slugs feed on the metallic minerals found in asteroids. They also happily=
 eat
  any passing space ships that they are able to catch.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Space
  slugs hide themselves in tunnels they bore into the rocky asteroids or
  planets they inhabit. They occasionally venture out, slithering across
  asteroids in search of prey. They can even jump short distances between
  asteroids, roaming across an asteroid field.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>They are
  slow-moving but pose a significant threat to stationary platforms like mi=
ning
  stations. When building mining stations in asteroid fields it is wise to
  patrol the new mining station until you are certain that no space slugs a=
re
  hiding in the field.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
